  "texts": [
    "Based on the previous analysis, the behavioral model of habit that underlies human moral practice has a function analogous to the emergence and homogenization characteristics of LLMs.",
    "LLMs can automatically generate corresponding text for similar questions in a stable manner.",
    "Humans learn practical knowledge of morality with the involvement of impulse and intelligence, through evaluation and rewards and punishments from others, and these also resemble the RLHF process.",
    "Just as humans continually reconstruct habits with impulse and intelligence, eventually forming character, LLMs also consistently align through RLHF, ultimately reaching Aligned AI-a \"human-machine hybrid\" encompassing human moral values and experience.",
    "The isomorphic relationship between human and LLM moral growth is shown in Table 12."
  ]
